{"title_page": "2020 in rail transport", "text_new": "{{Future year in rail transport|Rail transport 2020|prev=2019|curr=2020|next=2021|decade=2020}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n\n==Events==\n===January===\n* {{Flagicon|Canada}} '''January''' \u2013 The [[Deux-Montagnes line]] is being converted from [[commuter rail]] to [[light metro]] as part of the Reseau express metropolitain network.\n* {{Flagicon|USA}} '''January 26''' \u2013 SEPTA temporarily discontinues the [[SEPTA Route 15|Girard Avenue Trolley]] in [[Philadelphia]] for a period of at least 18 months due to rolling stock maintenance issues as well as track repairs and highway expansion.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://whyy.org/articles/septa-taking-girard-ave-trolley-off-the-rails-78-of-fleet-cant-pass-inspection/|title=SEPTA taking Girard Ave. trolley off the rails; 78 percent of fleet can\u2019t pass inspection |date=January 2020 |access-date=2020-01-23 |df= }}</ref>\n* {{Flagicon|New Zealand}} '''January 29''' \u2013 [[NZR V class]] [[steam locomotive]] no. 127 (built in Manchester, England, 1885) is recovered from the [[Oreti River]] in New Zealand by the [[Lumsden Heritage Trust]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Evan|last=Harding|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/motoring/news/119115296/rare-locomotives-pulled-from-river-bank-in-northern-southland|title=Rare locomotive pulled from river bank in Northern Southland|work=Stuff|location=Fairfax|date=2020-01-29|accessdate=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n* '''January 31'''\n**{{Flagicon|Singapore}} \u2013 [[Thomson\u2013East Coast MRT line|Thomson\u2013East Coast MRT Line]] Stage 1 opened.<ref name=\"\u5c65\u52d8\">{{cite news|publisher=\u4e2d\u592e\u793e|title=\u4ea4\u901a\u90e828\u65e5\u5b9a\u74b0\u72c0\u7dda\u5c65\u52d8\u65e5 \u78ba\u5b9a\u7121\u6cd5\u5e74\u5e95\u901a\u8eca|url=https://www.cna.com.tw/news/firstnews/201912235003.aspx|date=2019-12-23}}</ref>\n** {{flagicon|Taiwan}} \u2013 Opening of Taipei Metro [[Circular line (Taipei Metro)|Circular Line (First Section)]].<re