ns]], a publicly owned [[operator of last resort]], takes over the Northern passenger train operating franchise in England from [[Arriva Rail North]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.railwaygazette.com/uk/no-immediate-changes-to-follow-northern-nationalisation/55651.article|title=No immediate changes to follow Northern nationalisation.|website=[[Railway Gazette]]|date=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|France}} '''March 5'''\u2013 [[2020 Ingenheim derailment]]\n* {{flagicon|Japan}} '''March 8''' \u2013 [[700 Series Shinkansen]] is expected to retire from the [[Tokaido Shinkansen]].\n* {{flagicon|Japan}} '''March 13''' - last day of operations for [[Odoriko|Super View Odoriko]] services. JR East phrasing out the [[251 series]] \n*'''March 14''' \n**{{flagicon|Japan}} - [[Takanawa Gateway Station]] in Tokyo commerences operation on the [[Yamanote Line|Yamanote]] and [[Keihin Tohoku Line|Keihin Tohoku]] Lines. \n**{{flagicon|Japan}} - JR East begins [[Odoriko|Saphir Odoriko]] limited express services between [[Tokyo Station|Tokyo]] or [[Shinjuku Station|Shinjuku]] and [[Izuky\u016b Shimoda Station]], using the new [[E261 series]] . \n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} '''March 22'''  \u2013 [[Manchester Metrolink]] [[Trafford Park Line]] opened.<ref>[https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/people-greater-manchester-urged-not-17957387 People in Greater Manchester urged not to use public transport for anything other than \u2018essential journeys, with services to be \u2018stepped down\u2019 from Sunday] ''[[Manchester Evening News]]'' 21 March 2020</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Australia}} \u2013 Completion of [[CBD and South East Light Rail]] Kingsford branch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/sydney-s-troubled-light-rail-line-set-for-staged-opening-to-passengers-20190306-p5122t.html|title=Sydney's troubled light rail line set for staged opening to passengers|last=O'Sullivan|first=Matt|date=2019-03-07|website=The Sydney Morning Herald