2010s).{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n* {{flagicon|China}} \u2013 Total length of the [[Guangzhou Metro]] will exceed 600 km.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n* {{flagicon|Serbia}} \u2013 Expected start of operation Belgrade\u2013Stara Pazova section at 200k/h.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|Thailand}} \u2013 [[Gold Line (Bangkok)]] opening.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 [[East Coast Main Line]] to be equipped with [[ERTMS]] Level 2 signalling between London King's Cross and Doncaster, with possible speed increase from 125 mph to 140 mph. {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 [[Grand Central (train operating company)|Grand Central's]] [[Euston railway station|Euston]] to [[Blackpool North railway station|Blackpool]] service scheduled to commence.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 Planned rolling stock replacement for [[Island Line, Isle of Wight]], using [[British Rail Class 484|Class 484]] units. [[British Rail Class 483|Class 483]] to be withdrawn after being 82 years in service.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 Electrification of [[Midland Mainline]] reaches Sheffield, the project is claimed to be completed.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 [[Thameslink Programme]] to be completed, after being proposed in 1997 and started in 2009. Train services through London from north to south to provide increased 12-car capacity. The longest commuter train in the UK by its length to start service.\n*{{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 [[Los Angeles County Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]'s [[Crenshaw/LAX Line]] expected to open,<ref>{{cite news |title=Metro's Crenshaw/LAX Line opening delayed to 2020 |last1=Chiland |first1=Elijah |url=https://la.curbed.com/2018/11/16/18097780/metro-crenshaw-lax-line-opening-date-2020-delay |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |agency=Curbed |date=November 16, 2018}}</ref> including [[Aviation/Century (Los Angeles Metro 