t of line to be upgraded from 90 mph to 110 mph speed, the same speed ranges as it were on this line in 1930s.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 New Brunswick to Trenton, Pennsylvania upgrades to be completed after 1-year delay. [[Northeast Corridor]] speeds to be increased to 160 mph, making it true high-speed line by UIC classification. Some time after it, further upgrades to 186 mph are approved.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 [[Texas Central Railway]] expected to begin construction on a [[high-speed rail]] system between Houston and Dallas.\n* {{flagicon|USA}} '''Q3''' \u2013 [[XpressWest]] construction to break ground in California.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilson |first1=Bill |title=Virgin Trains USA could start construction of high-speed line in Calif., Nev., in late 2020 |url=https://www.rtands.com/railroad-news/virgin-trains-usa-could-start-construction-of-high-speed-line-in-calif-nev-in-late-2020/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |agency=RT&S |date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|USA}} '''Fall''' \u2013 The [[Washington Metro]] [[Silver Line (Washington Metro)|Silver Line]] is tentatively planned to be extended to [[Ashburn station (Washington Metro)|Ashburn station]] via [[Washington Dulles International Airport]], though delays are possible.<ref>{{cite news |last1=George |first1=Justin |title=Metro releases first operating budget for Silver Line extension |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-releases-first-operating-budget-for-silver-line-extension/2020/01/13/3b7b89e2-3624-11ea-9541-9107303481a4_story.html |accessdate=18 January 2020 |agency=Washington Post |date=28 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Max |title=New details on Silver Line concrete, software issues that could contribute to opening delay |url=https://wtop.com/tracking-metro-24-7/2020/01/new-details-on-silver-line-concrete-software-issues-that-could-contribute-to-opening-delay/ |accessdate=18 January