 Line]] estimated completion.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} '''March 22'''  \u2013 [[Manchester Metrolink]] [[Trafford Park Line]] opened.<ref>[https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/people-greater-manchester-urged-not-17957387 People in Greater Manchester urged not to use public transport for anything other than \u2018essential journeys, with services to be \u2018stepped down\u2019 from Sunday] ''[[Manchester Evening News]]'' 21 March 2020</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Australia}} \u2013 Completion of [[CBD and South East Light Rail]] Kingsford branch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/nsw/sydney-s-troubled-light-rail-line-set-for-staged-opening-to-passengers-20190306-p5122t.html|title=Sydney's troubled light rail line set for staged opening to passengers|last=O'Sullivan|first=Matt|date=2019-03-07|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Sweden}} \u2013 [[Flixtrain]] plans to begin operating long-distance passenger services from [[Stockholm]].<ref name=WtGWtS20/>\n\n===April===\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}{{flagicon|France}}{{flagicon|Germany}}{{flagicon|Poland}}{{flagicon|Belarus}}{{flagicon|Russia}}{{flagicon|North Korea}} '''April 28\u2013May 24''' \u2013 A rail special excursion will run from [[Wigan]] to [[Pyongyang]], [[North Korea]].<ref>https://www.ladbible.com/news/news-you-can-now-get-a-train-from-wigan-to-north-korea-20190523</ref>\n\n===May===\n*{{flagicon|Bulgaria}} \u2013 [[Sofia Metro]] Line 3 is expected to open.<ref>{{cite news |title=The First Section of the New Metro Line Starts Operating in May |url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/203216/The+First+Section+of+the+New+Metro+Line+Starts+Operating+in+May |accessdate=21 February 2020 |agency=Novinite |date=18 February 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|Mexico}} \u2013 Expected opening of Line 3 in the [[Guadalajara light rail system]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jorge |first1=Mar\u00ednez |title=L\u