020}}\n*{{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 Electrification of [[Midland Mainline]] reaches Sheffield, the project is claimed to be completed.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} \u2013 [[Thameslink Programme]] to be completed, after being proposed in 1997 and started in 2009. Train services through London from north to south to provide increased 12-car capacity. The longest commuter train in the UK by its length to start service.\n*{{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 [[Los Angeles County Metropolitan Transportation Authority]]'s [[Crenshaw/LAX Line]] expected to open,<ref>{{cite news |title=Metro's Crenshaw/LAX Line opening delayed to 2020 |last1=Chiland |first1=Elijah |url=https://la.curbed.com/2018/11/16/18097780/metro-crenshaw-lax-line-opening-date-2020-delay |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |agency=Curbed |date=November 16, 2018}}</ref> including [[Aviation/Century (Los Angeles Metro station)|Aviation/Century station]]. Though this may be delayed.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fine |first1=Howard |title=Waiting Game |url=https://labusinessjournal.com/news/2020/mar/06/metro-delays-crenshaw-lax-rail-line-again/ |accessdate=9 March 2020 |agency=Los Angeles Business Journal |date=6 March 2020}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 Tentative opening of the [[Berryessa station (BART)|Berryessa]] segment of the [[Silicon Valley BART extension]].<ref name= \"SJ Mercury 2019October\" >{{cite news |url= https://www.mercurynews.com/2019/10/01/san-jose-bart-delay-milpitas-berryessa-stations-likely-to-miss-2019-opening/ |title = San Jose BART delay: Milpitas, Berryessa stations likely to miss 2019 opening: Officials had hoped to open the stations by the end of the year |newspaper = San Jose Mercury News |date= October 1, 2019 |quote= But the agency\u2019s general manager revealed this week that BART is likely to miss that target, and trains probably won\u2019t start taking passengers to those stations until sometime in 2020. |accessdate= October 10, 2019}}</ref><ref name= \"SF chron 2019October\" >{{cite news |url= https://www.sfgate.com/local/article/milpitas-berryessa-bart-opening-date-delay-14484197.php |title = Are the Milpitas and Berryessa BART stations going to open on time? It's complicated. |newspaper = San Francisco Chronicle |date= October 1, 2019 |quote= Revenue service will not start on Dec. 28, 2019 if VTA does not resolve the discrepancies necessary for BART to start pre-revenue testing by Oct. 21, 2019 |accessdate= October 10, 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|USA}} &ndash; [[Tri-Rail]] Downtown Miami Link is expected to open.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tri-Rail Downtown Miami Link Service |url=https://www.tri-rail.com/pages/view/downtown-miami-link |website=Tri Rail |publisher=Southern Florida Regional Transportation Authority |accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 Chicago to St. Louis railway to be equipped with Positive Train Control. Most of line to be upgraded from 90 mph to 110 mph speed, the same speed ranges as it were on this line in 1930s.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 New Brunswick to Trenton, Pennsylvania upgrades to be completed after 1-year delay. [[Northeast Corridor]] speeds to be increased to 160 mph, making it true high-speed line by UIC classification. Some time after it, further upgrades to 186 mph are approved.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} \u2013 [[Texas Central Railway]] expected to begin construction on a [[high-speed rail]] system between Houston and Dallas.\n* {{flagicon|USA}} '''Q3''' \u2013 [[XpressWest]] construction to break ground in California.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wilson |first1=Bill |title=Virgin Trains USA could start construction of high-speed line in Calif., Nev., in late 2020 |url=https://www.rtands.com/railroad-news/virgin-trains-usa-could-start-construction-of-high-speed-line-in-calif-nev-in-late-2020/ |accessdate=27 December 2019 |agency=RT&S |date=16 December 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|USA}} '''Fall''' \u2013 The [[Washington Metro]] [[Silver Line (Washington Metro)|Silver Line]] is tentatively planned to be extended to [[Ashburn station (Washington Metro)|Ashburn station]] via [[Washington Dulles International Airport]], though delays are possible.<ref>{{cite news |last1=George |first1=Justin |title=Metro releases first operating budget for Silver Line extension |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-releases-first-operating-budget-for-silver-line-extension/2020/01/13/3b7b89e2-3624-11ea-9541-9107303481a4_story.html |accessdate=18 January 2020 |agency=Washington Post |date=28 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Max |title=New details on Silver Line concrete, software issues that could contribute to opening delay |url=https://wtop.com/tracking-metro-24-7/2020/01/new-details-on-silver-line-concrete-software-issues-that-could-contribute-to-opening-delay/ |accessdate=18 January 2020 |publisher=WTOP |date=17 January 2020}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon|USA}} &ndash; The [[Center City Corridor (LYNX)|Center City Corridor]] of the [[LYNX Rapid Transit Services|LYNX]] transportation network in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]], is scheduled to open.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Harper |first1=Briana |title=Neighbors in Elizabeth concerned about ongoing streetcar construction |url=https://www.wcnc.com/article/news/local/neighbors-elizabeth-concerned-ongoing-streetcar-construction/275-5559fc41-4ac5-4ca9-a488-36eb16f98b37 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |agency=WCNC |publisher=NBC |date=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2020 railway accidents}}\n[[Category:2020 in rail transport| ]]\n[[Category:2020-related timelines]]\n\n{{rail-transport-stub}}\n{{year-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Numberguy6", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMarch:Pakistan line did not open on scheduled date.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_in_rail_transport"}
{"title_page": "Cl\u00e1udio Ramos", "text_new": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Cl\u00e1udio Ramos\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Cl\u00e1udio Pires Morais Ramos \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1991|11|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vila Nova de Paiva]], [[Portugal]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]]\n| clubnumber = 1\n| youthyears1 = 2002\u20132005 | youthclubs1 = Paivense\n| youthyears2 = 2005\u20132006 | youthclubs2 = [[Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu FC|Acad\u00e9mico Viseu]]\n| youthyears3 = 2006 | youthclubs3 = Repesenses\n| youthyears4 = 2007\u20132010 | youthclubs4 = [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Guimar\u00e3es]]\n| years1 = 2010\u20132012 | clubs1 = [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria Guimar\u00e3es]] | caps1 = 0 | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2010\u20132011 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Amarante F.C.|Amarante]] (loan) | caps2 = 16 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2011\u20132012 | clubs3 = \u2192 [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] (loan) | caps3 = 7 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2012\u2013 | clubs4 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps4 = 231 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2007 | nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-16 football team|Portugal U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2008 | nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 1 | nationalgoals2 = 0 \n| nationalyears3 = 2008\u20132009 | nationalteam3 = [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2010 | nationalteam4 = [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal U20]] | nationalcaps4 = 2 | nationalgoals4 = 0 \n| nationalyears5 = 2018\u2013 | nationalteam5 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] | nationalcaps5 = 1 | nationalgoals5 = 0\n| club-update = 15 February 2020\n| nationalteam-update = 14 October 2018\n}}\n'''Cl\u00e1udio Pires Morais Ramos''' (born 16 November 1991) is a Portuguese [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[C.D. Tondela]] as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].\n\nHe spent most of his career with [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]], having signed in 2011 initially on a loan deal during the 2011-2012 season before making a permeant move  for the 2012-2013 season ([https://www.transfermarkt.co.uk/claudio-ramos/profil/spieler/155396]\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Vila Nova de Paiva]], [[Viseu District]], Ramos played for [[Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu F.C.]] in his hometown as a youth before moving to [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.]] in 2007. He never played a senior game for the team from [[Guimar\u00e3es]] and was loaned to [[Amarante F.C.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gmrtv.pt/atualidade/2155-oficial-vitoria-contrata-guarda-redes-assis-e-cede-o-ao-lousada|title=OFICIAL {{!}} Vit\u00f3ria contrata guarda-redes Assis e cede-o ao Lousada|trans-title=OFFICIAL {{!}} Vit\u00f3ria sign goalkeeper Assis and loan him to Lousada|publisher=Guimar\u00e3es TV|language=Portuguese|date=24 August 2010|accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> and [[C.D. Tondela]], who he joined permanently after winning promotion from the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]] in the [[2011\u201312 Segunda Divis\u00e3o|2011\u201312 season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/nao-profissional/noticias/interior/tondela-sobe-a-ii-liga-e-faz-historia-2583104.html|title=Tondela sobe \u00e0 II Liga e faz hist\u00f3ria|trans-title=Tondela promote to II League and make history|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|language=Portuguese|date=3 June 2012|accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/claudio-ramos-renova-por-dois-anos-com-o-tondela|title=Cl\u00e1udio Ramos renova por dois anos com o Tondela|trans-title=Cl\u00e1udio Ramos renews with Tondela for two years|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=Portuguese|date=11 June 2015|accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2018/09/28/claudio-ramos-fez-o-que-quase-nunca-faz-e-decidiu-o-jogo/|title=Cl\u00e1udio Ramos fez o que quase nunca faz e decidiu o jogo|trans-title=Cl\u00e1udio Ramos did what he rarely ever does and decided the match|newspaper=Observador|first=Mariana|last=Fernandes|language=Portuguese|date=28 September 2018|accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nTondela reached the [[Primeira Liga]] for the first time in [[2014\u201315 Segunda Liga|2014\u201315]], and Ramos made his debut in the competition on 30 October 2015 in a 0\u20134 home loss against [[S.L. Benfica]] after [[Matt Jones (footballer, born 1986)|Matt Jones]] suffered an injury at the 30-minute mark.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2015/10/30/benfica-vai-aveiro-sossegar-tripulacao/|title=Come\u00e7ou aos 4\u2032, acabou aos quatro golos. O Benfica quase nem teve que suar \u2013 como aconteceu|trans-title=It started on the 4th, it ended at four goals. Benfica hardly had to sweat it \u2013 how it happened|newspaper=Observador|first=Tiago|last=Palma|language=Portuguese|date=30 October 2015|accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref> During the 2016-2017 summer transfer window there was rumours of interest from an Edinburgh Club hopeful you sign the in form goal keeper however this did not materialise due to the players high wages [https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/claudio-ramos_prs237131/person.shtml]. In the [[2017\u201318 Primeira Liga|2017\u201318 campaign]] he played all 34 matches, and the last one was his 200th for the club, making him the second-most used player in their history. He also led the league in saves (126) and penalty saves (three) that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20172018/noticias/geral/liga-tv-totalista-claudio-ramos-completou-200-jogos-pelo-cd-tondela/|title=LIGA TV: Totalista Cl\u00e1udio Ramos completou 200 jogos pelo CD Tondela|trans-title=LIGA TV: Ever-present Cl\u00e1udio Ramos completed 200 games for CD Tondela|publisher=Liga Portugal|language=Portuguese|date=13 May 2018|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nRamos made his senior debut for [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 14 October 2018 in a 3\u20131 friendly win over [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at [[Hampden Park]], playing the last four minutes as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Beto (footballer, born 1982)|Beto]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/estreia-tambem-para-pedro-mendes-e-claudio-ramos?ref=Pesquisa_Destaques|title=Estreia tamb\u00e9m para Pedro Mendes e Cl\u00e1udio Ramos|trans-title=Debut as well for Pedro Mendes and Cl\u00e1udio Ramos|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]|first=Lu\u00eds|last=Miroto Sim\u00f5es|language=Portuguese|date=14 October 2018|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*[https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/672207 National team data] {{in lang|pt}}\n*{{NFT player|id=72259}}\n*{{Soccerway|claudio-pires-morais-ramos/134604}}\n\n{{C.D. Tondela squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramos, Claudio}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Viseu]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:Vit\u00f3ria S.C. players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Tondela players]]\n[[Category:Portugal youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Portugal international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Portuguese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Cl\u00e1udio Ramos\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Cl\u00e1udio Pires Morais Ramos \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1991|11|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vila Nova de Paiva]], [[Portugal]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| posi